body:
hi @deplabcut (funny name choice ;). Are your evaluation images (i..e, the images you labeled) moved? if you search there error, there are two related issues, did you check those out? 

https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut/search?q=ValueError%3A+Cannot+feed+value+of+shape%22&type=issues

Hello @MMathisLab, thank you so much for this response. I did see the related issues, but didn't know how to implement the changes you mentioned (i.e. changing the number of color channels) since I'm using the GUI, and not the terminal.

Also, I don't believe the images I labeled were moved: they are still in the labeled-data folder. Within the labeled data folder, they are in a folder called [videoname-labeled].

Sorry, I'm new to this, and thank you so much!

Also, there are two separate subfolders folders in the labeled-data (video and video_labeled_data), so I don't believed anything was overwritten. 

I'm also using the latest version of DLC. I followed the youtube tutorial and only labeled two corners of the box I was looking at; could this be the problem?

I think it may be a color channel issue because when I click the "optional: plot 3 test maps" option, the images I get in the maps folder in the evaluation-results folder are tinted purple and green, which was not my original color. Also, these pictures are only those which I have labeled, not new pictures.

> Also, there are two separate subfolders folders in the labeled-data (video and video_labeled_data), so I don't believed anything was overwritten.

The folder with just the video name is the important one. The one with `labeled` is the result of running `check_labels`. You should inspect those images to make sure the markers are being placed where you want them. After inspection, you can actually delete those 'labeled' folders if you want (e.g. to save space).

>Also, I don't believe the images I labeled were moved: they are still in the labeled-data folder. Within the labeled data folder, they are in a folder called [videoname-labeled].

Not that folder. Make sure the images are in the folders just named for the video.

>I'm also using the latest version of DLC. 

If you are running this on your mac, activate your env, then:
```
pythonw
import deeplabcut
deeplabcut.__version__
```
It would be very helpful if you provide the actual version number. Or are you using colab to train and evaluate?

>I followed the youtube tutorial and only labeled two corners of the box I was looking at; could this be the problem?

Yes, if  you don't have any animal body parts labeled. What specifically do you have entered in config.yaml for bodyparts? If you don't have any animal body parts there, or have them but didn't label any, you should expect errors. 

>I am using multi animal mode but I'm only evaluating a single animal.

If you are new to deeplabcut, I would strongly advise against this until you have fully trained a single animal model for your scenario and determined that it is insufficient and the added features of the multi-animal tracking might be beneficial. However, using maDLC for single animal is about to get quite a bit smoother.

> (1, 1796, 2412, 4)

You also appear to have very large frames. Did you increase `max_input_size` to 2412 (or more) in `pose_cfg.yaml` in both test and train folders in dlc-models? With maDLC now doing autocropping for training, I don't think this should cause any problems, at least for training, but it might be worth changing it anyways.

@MMathisLab Thank you very much for this response. 

I confirmed that the subfolder of just the video name in the labeled-data folder has only the unlabeled pictures, as well as a data collected csv and h5 file. 

Also, it says the version I have for deeplabcut is 2.2.0.3. I am using my mac terminal, not colab.

The video I was using is called "Using maDLC/ DeepLabCut 2.2 with a *single animal*," and I have the same config.yaml (multianimal) file as in the video, and the bodyparts part is:

individuals:
- individual1
uniquebodyparts:
- cornerofbox1
- cornerofbox2
multianimalbodyparts:
- snout
- leftear
- rightear
- midbody
- tailbase
- tail
skeleton:
- - snout
  - leftear
- - snout
  - rightear
- - snout
  - midbody
- - snout
  - tailbase
- - midbody
  - tailbase
- - leftear
  - rightear
- - leftear
  - midbody
- - rightear
  - midbody
- - midbody
  - tail1
- - tailbase
  - tail1

Also, I didn't see a line called max_input_size in the pose_cfg.yaml for test. I have added a line called max_input_size: 2412 in this yaml file and increased the max_input_size to 2412 for the train folder pose_cfg.yaml file. Thanks for the help!

It's very doable to use maDLC with single animals (I have multiple projects run that way), but I wouldn't recommend it until you know that standard DLC isn't sufficient. 

>I followed the youtube tutorial and only labeled two corners of the box I was looking at; could this be the problem?

I read that to mean that you labeled only the two box corners, and **not** any of the multianimalbodyparts. Did you label all the body parts in all of the images?

@backyardbiomech I labeled all of the bodyparts for the single animal in each frame. However, sometimes the animal was blocking the corner of a box, so I didn't label that corner. Is this problematic? Or should I retrain/relabel the corner of a box over the mouse that's blocking it in all frames? Thanks

> I labeled all of the bodyparts for the single animal in each frame. 
Good. So that's not the problem.

> Or should I retrain/relabel the corner of a box over the mouse that's blocking it in all frames?
No. As a general rule, only label what you can see. 

> Also, I didn't see a line called max_input_size in the pose_cfg.yaml for test
I can't always remember what is in each without looking. Adding it shouldn't cause a problem, though. Did that fix the evaluation problem? @MMathisLab would know if this large size would still be a problem with the cropping in maDLC, but you might need to train anew now that you've changed it.

@backyardbiomech Haven't fixed the evaluation problem yet-- been stuck on this for a while. When I hit the "RUN: Evaluate network" button in the GUI, the terminal continues to say:


Activating extracting of PAFs
Network Evaluation underway...
0it [00:00, ?it/s]
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/Users/user/opt/anaconda3/envs/DEEPLABCUT/lib/python3.8/site-packages/deeplabcut/gui/evaluate_network.py", line 270, in evaluate_network
    deeplabcut.evaluate_network(
  File "/Users/user/opt/anaconda3/envs/DEEPLABCUT/lib/python3.8/site-packages/deeplabcut/pose_estimation_tensorflow/core/evaluate.py", line 572, in evaluate_network
    evaluate_multianimal_full(
  File "/Users/user/opt/anaconda3/envs/DEEPLABCUT/lib/python3.8/site-packages/deeplabcut/pose_estimation_tensorflow/core/evaluate_multianimal.py", line 350, in evaluate_multianimal_full
    pred = predictma.predict_batched_peaks_and_costs(
  File "/Users/user/opt/anaconda3/envs/DEEPLABCUT/lib/python3.8/site-packages/deeplabcut/pose_estimation_tensorflow/core/predict_multianimal.py", line 215, in predict_batched_peaks_and_costs
    scmaps, locrefs, *pafs, peaks = sess.run(
  File "/Users/user/opt/anaconda3/envs/DEEPLABCUT/lib/python3.8/site-packages/tensorflow/python/client/session.py", line 970, in run
    result = self._run(None, fetches, feed_dict, options_ptr,
  File "/Users/user/opt/anaconda3/envs/DEEPLABCUT/lib/python3.8/site-packages/tensorflow/python/client/session.py", line 1167, in _run
    raise ValueError(
ValueError: Cannot feed value of shape (1, 1796, 2412, 4) for Tensor Placeholder:0, which has shape (1, None, None, 3)
Also, is there a way to remove markers when labeling?
If it is indeed a color channel issue as mentioned in other posts, would there by anyway to change the shape of Tensor Placeholder:0?
